Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.67,0:00:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.55,0:00:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, she was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.51,0:00:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,She's fallen on pretty hard times,\Nbut her attitude is as bad as before.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.84,0:00:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's gotten even worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.93,0:00:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Did she say where she's staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.52,0:00:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She said\Nshe didn't have any cash with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.77,0:00:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so she told me to go to\Nher hotel if I wanted to get paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.44,0:00:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,She still thinks she's a princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.49,0:00:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Which hotel is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.70,0:00:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I think she said it was Hotel Staigent.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.53,0:00:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If she's staying at a third-rate hotel\Nlike that, I doubt I'll ever get paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.12,0:00:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait…
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.75,0:00:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you the guy who was engaged to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.88,0:00:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.26,0:00:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Police? That guy\Nwanted for murder was just here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.31,0:00:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,-Hey!\N-Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.22,0:00:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's my coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.35,0:01:01.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I hung it on the rack by the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.52,0:03:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.57,0:03:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I think there's a woman\Nnamed Eva Heinemann staying at your hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.57,0:03:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'll connect you to her room.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.03,0:03:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.58,0:03:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.58,0:03:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,CREDIT: DM 300
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.71,0:03:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.59,0:03:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,CREDIT: DM 150
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.09,0:03:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.05,0:03:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I'm going to kill…
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.09,0:03:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,your ex-fiancée, Eva Heinemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.27,0:03:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for waiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.56,0:03:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I rang her room, but she didn't answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.44,0:03:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,What's her room number?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.57,0:03:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to send her a fax,\Nso could you give me her room number?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.03,0:03:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.28,0:04:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Her room number is 402.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.24,0:04:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fax number is…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.63,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,402…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.31,0:04:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.68,0:04:29.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Baul's not in his office\Nand isn't answering his phone either.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.31,0:04:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I doubt your partner will show up\Nno matter how long we wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.82,0:04:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is why I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.57,0:04:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He became Tenma's lawyer\Nto prove his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.53,0:04:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But then Tenma confessed to everything,\Nand to make things worse, he escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.25,0:04:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He probably thinks there's no way\Nhe can defend Tenma,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.87,0:04:52.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so he's dropping him as his client.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.51,0:05:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you drop him too, Mr. Verdemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.93,0:05:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I won't.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.68,0:05:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Tenma has now escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.48,0:05:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish he had trusted me\Nto help him before he escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.02,0:05:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So you believe in Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.03,0:05:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe what happened in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe everything\Nthat Tenma told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.99,0:05:28.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know what I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.50,0:05:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that you don't believe any of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.42,0:05:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard the news of Tenma's escape,\Nit felt the same as what happened before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.55,0:05:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It felt like when he disappeared in Munich\Nto go and assassinate Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.77,0:05:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something he's trying to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.85,0:05:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why Tenma escaped!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.52,0:05:57.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe in him!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.19,0:06:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Believe in him like you did your father,\Nwhich led you to become a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.74,0:06:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The phone's been ringing off the hook!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The media's going crazy asking
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.75,0:06:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,if the great attorney Verdemann\Nwill continue to defend Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.00,0:06:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them that I have no comment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.13,0:06:23.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can't keep the press\Nat bay for long just saying that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.80,0:06:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Then tell them\Nwe'll hold a press conference
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.47,0:06:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,after I've reviewed\Nall the facts in this case again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.02,0:06:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then,\Ndon't let anyone into the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.02,0:06:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But you already got a visitor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.73,0:06:38.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You're kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.07,0:06:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You let them in?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.69,0:06:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not seeing anyone today!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.24,0:06:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I know. I told him so\Nand tried to turn him away,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.37,0:06:48.54,Default,,0,0,0,,but he forced his way in\Nand said he'd wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.37,0:06:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who the heck is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's from the Federal Police.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.92,0:06:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,BKA?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.55,0:07:05.14,Default,,0,0,0,,"Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.80,0:07:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Such a lovely song.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.93,0:07:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, it was the theme song\Nof your father's radio station.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.73,0:07:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.94,0:07:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.32,0:07:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,406.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.36,0:07:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,405.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.95,0:07:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,404.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.75,0:07:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Room 402.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.21,0:07:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.30,0:07:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Guten tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.60,0:07:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Guten tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.91,0:08:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,-Excuse me.\N-What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.12,0:08:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's the guest staying in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.12,0:08:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.33,0:08:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come to visit the guest staying here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.13,0:08:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Haven't they already checked out?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.51,0:08:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,See? There's nobody here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.40,0:08:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Eva…
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.44,0:08:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Inspector Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.40,0:08:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I've looked through many\Nof Tenma's police statement records.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.28,0:08:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yours was one of those\Nthat I had a careful look at.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.37,0:08:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an extremely detailed report.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also heard rumors about you,\Nthe darling of the legal world,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.96,0:09:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.13,0:09:05.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure you came to me\Nafter hearing about Tenma's escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.71,0:09:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.38,0:09:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I have absolutely no information\Nabout it that I can offer you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.39,0:09:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,He escaped, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.76,0:09:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in the middle\Nof an extended vacation right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.27,0:09:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You could even call this long vacation\Nan escape of sorts for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.65,0:09:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll have to excuse me,\Nbut I don't have time for small talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.16,0:09:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably out of habit\Nfrom working for so many years,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I cannot take a vacation\Nwithout any specific purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.83,0:09:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So I've developed\Na sort of theme for my vacation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.59,0:09:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme for this vacation\Nis this picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.55,0:09:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but I don't have time for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.55,0:09:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.93,0:09:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk a little longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.93,0:10:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you,\NI have nothing to say about Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.60,0:10:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I have not come here to talk about Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.23,0:10:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You see,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.57,0:10:13.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't hear about Tenma's escape\Nuntil I was on my way over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.53,0:10:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then why in the world are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As I said, it's about this picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.37,0:10:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I am deeply interested in learning more\Nabout the author of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.33,0:10:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the author had several pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.50,0:10:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The only one he used\Nthat was German is Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.88,0:10:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That intrigued me,\Nso when I looked into it,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.14,0:10:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I found that there was a certain person\Nwho Poppe was associated with.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.64,0:10:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What person was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.10,0:10:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.31,0:10:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father's radio station ran a show\Ncalled Fairy Tales of the World.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.65,0:10:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,According to records, in August 1966,\NPoppe's work Where Am I? was aired.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.83,0:11:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a look at the records\Nof your father's trial as well,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest post-war espionage case.\NA case that shook all of West Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.21,0:11:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.80,0:11:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father traveled\Nto Czechoslovakia several times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.26,0:11:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Since they were just meetings\Nwith a picture book author,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.60,0:11:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the prosecutor never mentioned them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.27,0:11:22.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.02,0:11:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me that your father was\Nold friends with this picture book author.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.52,0:11:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Due to his line of work,\Nmy father had lots of connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.99,0:11:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He met with\Nan infinite number of people for his show.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.07,0:11:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying that he wasn't\Na close acquaintance with Poppe?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.37,0:11:43.91,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I looked into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.00,0:11:48.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ordinarily, Klaus Poppe had meetings\Neither at his editor's home
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.33,0:11:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,or at an old farmhouse that served\Nas his villa in the Czech suburbs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.96,0:11:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But when your father met him,\Nthey met at a certain mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.84,0:11:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,A mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.35,0:12:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It was called the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.43,0:12:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But he never met people at that mansion\Nusing the name Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.65,0:12:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,When he used that mansion,\Nthe name he used was…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.82,0:12:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.82,0:12:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,He held a very important post\Nin the Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.38,0:12:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.38,0:12:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.76,0:12:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.97,0:12:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the son of a traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.35,0:12:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You son of a coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.65,0:12:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! If you don't like it,\Nthen prove that he didn't do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.94,0:12:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,If the father's scum, then his son is too!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:05.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I simply want to know\Nabout the man Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.38,0:13:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.88,0:13:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father met with the author\NKlaus Poppe at a certain mansion
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.80,0:13:24.05,Default,,0,0,0,,in Czechoslovakia in 1966.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.14,0:13:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Their only connection\Nis as a picture book author
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.31,0:13:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and a radio station owner!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.18,0:13:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,When he used the name Klaus Poppe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.40,0:13:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,he never once used the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you implying?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.19,0:13:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If your father met with that man\Nat the Red Rose Mansion,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.61,0:13:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,then the man\Nhe met with wasn't Klaus Poppe,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.87,0:13:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,but it was Franz Bonaparta,\Nthe man who held
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.46,0:13:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,an important position\Nin the Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.29,0:13:55.71,Default,,0,0,0,,These are false accusations!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.30,0:14:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care at all\Nwhether your father was a spy or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.80,0:14:03.72,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was no spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.80,0:14:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure your father was aware\Nof exactly who Franz Bonaparta was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.81,0:14:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,How is that relevant?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.31,0:14:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I think you know\Nwhat your father did when he went
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.32,0:14:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,No! You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.36,0:14:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is innocent! You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.95,0:14:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.86,0:14:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Please contact me\Nwhen you feel like talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.37,0:14:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me repeat
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.79,0:14:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have no interest whatsoever\Nin whether or not your father was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.92,0:14:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All I want to know is anything\Nrelating to Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.39,0:14:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,My father…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.39,0:14:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,My father…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.23,0:14:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Verdemann, your wife is on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:14:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.07,0:14:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.69,0:15:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Your wife is on the phone.\NShe's calling from the maternity ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.78,0:15:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.25,0:15:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.55,0:15:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that right?\NYou've been discharged? That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.59,0:15:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it. I'll head right over.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.41,0:15:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,-Tenma!\N-Start driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.79,0:15:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down! Listen to me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.08,0:15:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Start driving right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.33,0:15:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.84,0:16:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's talk this over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.34,0:16:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Just calm down\Nand tell me why you're doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.51,0:16:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.81,0:16:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Where's Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.52,0:16:18.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What's Eva Heinemann got to do with this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.19,0:16:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.56,0:16:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what you people are trying to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.19,0:16:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"You people"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.69,0:16:28.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop the car!\NEyes forward and keep driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.24,0:16:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you people want to take Eva's life!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.12,0:16:36.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"Take Eva's life"?\NWhat do you mean by "you people"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.50,0:16:37.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.00,0:16:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You and that partner of yours\Nwho calls himself Baul are in cahoots.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.09,0:16:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Baul?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.55,0:16:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the man I shot\Nat the library at Munich University!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.59,0:16:52.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let anyone else die!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.18,0:16:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me where you've taken Eva!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.35,0:16:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This all started when\NI saved Johan's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.52,0:17:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So many people have died since then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.52,0:17:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So many, many people!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.19,0:17:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take it anymore!\NI can't let anyone else die!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.91,0:17:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't stop the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.16,0:17:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.37,0:17:18.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I said drive!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.21,0:17:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is what you said just now true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.13,0:17:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I believe it's the truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.55,0:17:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,My father was convicted of being a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.52,0:17:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Later, he was exonerated.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.31,0:17:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But the truth is, he was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.32,0:17:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I believed my father was innocent,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.12,0:17:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I chose to be a lawyer\Nand studied very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.58,0:17:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But I found something\Nwhen I was in university.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.58,0:18:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I found irrefutable evidence\Nthat my father was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.67,0:18:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since then…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.42,0:18:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever since then,\NI couldn't believe anyone anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.63,0:18:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, the lawyer\Nwho gets his clients exonerated!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.55,0:18:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Me, the darling of the legal world!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.85,0:18:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What a joke! They've been fooled\Nby a man who doesn't believe anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.73,0:18:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You see…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.98,0:18:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the son of a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.20,0:18:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,When I found his notebook…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.33,0:18:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I found the notebook\Nmy father wrote in the 1960s.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.29,0:18:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,As I turned the pages\Nand read what was written in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.63,0:18:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,everything I'd built on my belief\Nin my father just crumbled away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.17,0:18:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,My father had,\Nwithout a doubt, been a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.43,0:19:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It was filled with an indecipherable code.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.10,0:19:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A record of his numerous meetings\Nwith the Czechoslovakia secret police.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.11,0:19:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My father met many mysterious people,\Nincluding Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.57,0:19:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he also write about\Nthe Red Rose Mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.70,0:19:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,How did you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.37,0:19:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.46,0:19:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That man Baul probably approached you
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.58,0:19:28.58,Default,,0,0,0,,because he wanted to\Nget his hands on that notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.59,0:19:31.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is that notebook now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.26,0:19:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,At my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.23,0:19:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.85,0:19:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt about it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.56,0:19:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He was after your father's notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,DEAR KENZO
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.11,0:19:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a letter for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.16,0:20:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have figured\Nthat you would come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.83,0:20:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,"Save me, Kenzo. Save me, Kenzo!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.21,0:20:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Come to the Red Rose Mansion quickly."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.04,0:20:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it mean Eva's safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.59,0:20:13.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.22,0:20:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't her writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.26,0:20:18.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He's toying with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.22,0:20:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That scum is toying with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.44,0:20:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.02,0:20:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It was among my pile of old records,\Ninside "Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.82,0:20:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.20,0:20:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.95,0:20:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But if it gets into anyone else's hands,\Nthe truth about your father will…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.46,0:20:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.08,0:20:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,FRÜHLING MATERNITY HOSPITAL
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.56,0:21:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I believe you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.53,0:21:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What you've told me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.86,0:21:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you're about to go and do,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.74,0:21:23.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't help you with those.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.08,0:21:27.50,Default,,0,0,0,,But can I believe you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.54,0:21:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone who carries one of these things,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.09,0:21:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you probably shouldn't believe.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.60,0:21:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to believe you.
